body: Yes, I'll also need ONNX export for `zero`, but that's not really an issue I think. No matter if they're implemented in ATen or not, if we want the export to be ONNX-compliant, we'll still need to add symbolic descriptions in `symbolic.py`. `zero(x)` can be e.g. desugared into `x - x`.
